    Range<T extends Object>
    Represents a value range, which can be open or closed at either end, or indefinite at either end. Examples: All numbers between zero and one (exclusive) - [0, 1) All strings between "S" and "T" (exclusive) - ["S", "T") All positive numbers - (0, ∞)

    Intervals are typically over {@link Comparable} objects, but they can also be over non-{@link Comparable} objects, if a {@link java.util.Comparator} is supplied to the range.
    RetryableException
    This class is a wrapper that suggests a behavior of the catcher. I.e., this error is an error in processing not an error in the object being processed. If this same process is attempted later it may succeeed. There are constructors that take a displaykey or string. There are also constructors that take a suggested retry time, if the creator can determine that. (i.e., if the service does not want to perform between 800 and 1600 this could be set to 1600) This is a wraper exception since there is a cause with the error information.

    SuspendableException
    This class is a wrapper that specifies the behavior of the catcher. I.e., this error is an error in processing not an error in the object being processed. If this same process is attempted later it may succeeed. This is different than RetryableException in that any object would receive the same error. This is a wraper exception since there is a cause with the error information
